						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Simply flip the texture coordinates or the vertex coordinates of the polygon you're drawing.</div><br /><br />Great suggestion. Done and it looks great! Thank you!<br /><br />I am curious though to my original question. Emulators which can't run at ~60 and have to drop frames... how do they manage to keep audio from staying in sync... or at least not sounding distorted if they drop a lot of frames?<br /><br />Or do you just need to make sure that your emulator is fast enough where that isn't a serious concern?</div>

