						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">rainwarrior wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">With no frameskip, every emulator I can think of just has gaps in the audio when it can't keep up to 60fps.</div><br />The really old emulators ran the sound channels (square, triangle, noise, DMC) asynchronously, so at the end of the frame, it could generate sound for as long as it needed to, or generate sound for whatever speed it needed to generate it at.  Usually the time to generate for would be about 1/60s.</div>

					
