				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Logging APU writes during the frame and then <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Catch-up" class="postlink">running them in a batch at the end</a> isn't even inaccurate, so long as all logged APU writes are timestamped with what CPU cycle they occurred on, and rendering reads those timestamps. It might even help with speed, as the audio stuff will fit more cleanly into the host CPU's cache. What got inaccurate in old emulators was that they in effect rounded timestamps to the nearest frame.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

